Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%pack}.

Arrange on a lined #baking tray{} and toss in a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Season
with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Bake until the chickpeas are crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Pop the @couscous{100%g} into a #medium bowl{}.

Add @water{200%ml}(boiling) to the bowl along with @Muscat{1%sachet}. Mix
thoroughly.

Cover with a #plate{} or cling film and leave aside for ~{10%minutes} or until
ready to serve.

Meanwhile, chop the @tomato{2}(chopped into 2cm chunks).

Halve, peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped).

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g}(chopped, stalks and all).

In a #large bowl{} for the salad, mix the @sweet chilli sauce{2%sachets},
juice of half the @lime{1}, half the parsley, @Apple Cider Vinegar{1%sachet}
and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{} and toss with the onion, tomato, chickpeas
and sweet chilli sauce.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%g}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to
taste}.

Fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.
> Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.
> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal
> due to vacuum packing we use to keep it fresh.

Divide the couscous between #bowls{}.

Crumble the @Greek Style Cheese{100%g} over.

Top with the golden chicken.

Garnish with the remaining parsley.